        {
          "attributes": {
            "response": "Here's what you need to know for your trip to Tokyo:\n\n1. **Time Zone**: Tokyo operates in Japan Standard Time (JST), which is UTC +9 hours. This is important to consider when planning your travel schedule and managing any necessary communications with those back home.\n\n2. **Local Currency**: The official currency in Tokyo is the Japanese Yen (JPY). Familiarize yourself with the exchange rate before traveling, and consider carrying some cash since some places may not accept credit cards.\n\n3. **Primary Language**: Japanese is the primary language spoken in Tokyo. While English is spoken in some areas, particularly tourist spots, it may be helpful to learn a few basic phrases in Japanese or bring a translation app for ease of communication.\n\n4. **Entry Requirements for US Citizens**: As a US citizen, you generally do not need a visa for short-term visits (up to 90 days). Your passport should be valid for the duration of your stay, and it's always a good idea to check for the latest travel advisories or requirement changes prior to your departure.\n\nPrepare well for your trip to enjoy all that Tokyo has to offer!"
          },
